# CeenAiX Coding Rules

## Project Context
This is CeenAiX — an AI-native healthcare platform for the UAE. Read `AGENTS.md` at the project root before making changes. Read `docs/agent/mvp-scope.md` for current build scope.

## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled — never use `any`
- Use interfaces for object shapes, types for unions/intersections
- All Supabase query results must be typed
- Define shared types in `src/types/`

## React Components
- Functional components only with TypeScript props interfaces
- Use named exports (exception: page components can use default export for lazy loading)
- Colocate component-specific hooks in the same file if small, or extract to `src/hooks/`
- Use React.lazy() for route-level code splitting
- Wrap page sections in ErrorBoundary components

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS utility classes only — no CSS modules, no styled-components, no inline style objects
- Use the CeenAiX design tokens: `ceenai-cyan`, `ceenai-blue`, `ceenai-navy` (defined in tailwind.config)
- Mobile-first responsive design: base styles for mobile, then `md:` and `lg:` breakpoints
- Use Tailwind logical properties (`ms-`, `me-`, `ps-`, `pe-`) instead of `ml-`, `mr-` for future RTL support

## Supabase
- Single Supabase client instance in `src/lib/supabase.ts`
- All queries in custom hooks (e.g., `useAppointments()`)
- Always handle loading, error, and empty states
- Every table MUST have RLS enabled — verify in migration files
- Use `auth.uid()` in RLS policies
- Soft delete for clinical data: `is_deleted` + `deleted_at`
- Include RLS policies in every migration that creates a table
- During MVP development, use canonical schema paths only. Do not add legacy compatibility code, fallback reads, or dual-schema support for Bolt-era fields/tables.

## Routing
- Route definitions in `src/lib/router.tsx`
- Patient routes: `/patient/*` — require role=patient
- Doctor routes: `/doctor/*` — require role=doctor
- Admin routes: `/admin/*` — require role=super_admin
- Public routes: `/`, `/ai-chat`, `/find-doctor`, `/find-clinic`, `/insurance`, `/health-education`
- Auth routes: `/auth/*`

## AI Integration
- NEVER call OpenAI or any AI API directly from frontend code
- All AI calls go through Supabase Edge Functions
- Stream AI responses using Server-Sent Events (SSE)
- Tag all AI-generated content in the UI with an "AI" label
- Check patient consent before injecting health data into AI context

## Database Migrations
- Place in `supabase/migrations/` with timestamp prefix
- Always include RLS policies for new tables
- Always include indexes on foreign key columns
- Use enums for status fields (defined as PostgreSQL types)
- Never drop clinical data columns — add new ones alongside

## Phase Awareness
- Current phase: MVP (Phase 1)
- DO NOT implement: video consultation, live transcription, family accounts, payments, Arabic/RTL, FCM push, nurse/pharmacy/lab/facility roles, DHA integration, UAE Pass, insurance claims, emergency access, analytics
- If asked about Phase 2+ features, confirm scope before implementing
